  "text": "Django's SQL injection prevention for raw SQL queries is implemented through a multi-layered approach using parameterized queries:\n\n### 1. RawSQL Expression Sanitization (django/db/models/expressions.py)\nThe RawSQL class (lines 1236-1268) is the primary mechanism for handling raw SQL expressions within Django ORM queries. It accepts SQL and parameters as separate arguments in its __init__ method, enforcing the separation of SQL structure from user input. The as_sql() method (line 1248) returns the SQL and params tuple separately, allowing the compiler to maintain this separation through the query compilation pipeline.\n\n### 2. raw() QuerySet Method Parameter Binding (django/db/models/query.py)\nThe QuerySet.raw() method (line 1461) enforces parameterized execution by accepting a params parameter that is passed through to RawQuerySet. The RawQuerySet class (line 2210) stores params separately from the raw_query and creates a RawQuery instance with both the SQL and params (line 2231). This design pattern ensures parameters remain distinct from the SQL query string throughout the query lifecycle.\n\n### 3. Cursor.execute() Parameterization Enforcement (django/db/models/sql/query.py and django/db/backends/utils.py)\nThe RawQuery._execute_query() method (line 203 in sql/query.py) is the critical enforcement point. It:\n- Adapts parameters based on their Python type using connection.ops.adapt_unknown_value (lines 208-217)\n- Executes the query using cursor.execute(self.sql, params) with SQL and params as separate arguments (line 220)\n\nThe CursorWrapper.execute() method (django/db/backends/utils.py, line 78) ensures all database operations use parameterized execution. The _execute() method (line 94) explicitly passes params separately to the underlying database driver's cursor.execute(), preventing any SQL injection opportunities.\n\n### 4. SQL Compiler Parameter Handling (django/db/models/sql/compiler.py)\nThe SQLCompiler.as_sql() method (line 763) generates SQL with placeholder syntax (%s, %(name)s, etc.) and maintains a separate params list. The execute_sql() method (line 1601) calls cursor.execute(sql, params) with the separated SQL and parameters (line 1631), delegating parameterization handling to the database driver.\n\n### 5. Parameter Type Adaptation (django/db/backends/base/operations.py)\nThe adapt_unknown_value() method (line 550) converts Python values to database-compatible types based on their Python type, not user input structure. This ensures type safety even for raw SQL queries where field types aren't explicitly declared.\n\n### Security Model Summary\nDjango's raw SQL injection prevention relies on:\n1. **Separation of Concerns**: SQL structure and parameters are kept separate at every layer\n2. **Database Driver Parameterization**: The separation is maintained all the way to the database driver's native parameterization mechanism\n3. **Type Safety**: Parameter values are adapted based on their Python type, not parsed from strings\n4. **Enforcement Points**: The cursor.execute() calls in both SQLCompiler and RawQuery enforce the parameterized pattern\n\nThis architecture ensures that even when developers use raw SQL with RawSQL expressions or the raw() method, the actual parameter binding is handled by the database driver, which is immune to SQL injection when parameters are passed separately from the query string."
}

